<ul><li><span class="texhtml"><i>C</i><sub><i>n</i></sub></span> is the number of <a href="/wiki/Young_tableau#Tableaux" title="Young tableau">standard Young tableaux</a> whose diagram is a 2-by-<span class="texhtml mvar" style="font-style:italic;">n</span> rectangle. In other words, it is the number of ways the numbers <span class="texhtml">1, 2, ..., 2<i>n</i></span> can be arranged in a 2-by-<span class="texhtml mvar" style="font-style:italic;">n</span> rectangle so that each row and each column is increasing. As such, the formula can be derived as a special case of the <a href="/wiki/Young_tableau#Dimension_of_a_representation" title="Young tableau">hook-length formula</a>.</li></ul>
<pre>123   124   125   134   135
456   356   346   256   246
</pre>
<ul><li><span class="texhtml"><i>C</i><sub><i>n</i></sub></span> is the number of length <span class="texhtml mvar" style="font-style:italic;">n</span> sequences  that start with 1, and can increase by either 0 or 1, or decrease by any number (to at least 1). For <span class="texhtml"><i>n</i> = 4</span> these are 1234, 1233, 1232, 1231, 1223, 1222, 1221, 1212, 1211, 1123, 1122, 1121, 1112, 1111. From a Dyck path, start a counter at 0. An X increases the counter by 1 and a Y decreases it by 1. Record the values at only the X's. Compared to the similar representation of the <a href="/wiki/Bell_number#Rhyme_schemes" title="Bell number">Bell numbers</a>, only 1213 is missing.</li></ul>
<div class="mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id="Proof_of_the_formula">Proof of the formula</h2><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Catalan_number&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3" title="Edit section: Proof of the formula"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>There are several ways of explaining why the formula
