is a generalization of the Catalan numbers. These are named <b>super-Catalan numbers</b>, per <a href="/wiki/Ira_Gessel" title="Ira Gessel">Ira Gessel</a>. These should not  confused with the <a href="/wiki/Schr%C3%B6der%E2%80%93Hipparchus_number" title="Schröder–Hipparchus number">Schröder–Hipparchus numbers</a>, which sometimes are also called super-Catalan numbers.
</p><p>For <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle m=1}">
