and it is an open problem to find a general combinatorial interpretation.
</p><p><a href="/wiki/Sergey_Fomin" title="Sergey Fomin">Sergey Fomin</a> and Nathan Reading have given a generalized Catalan number associated to any finite crystallographic <a href="/wiki/Coxeter_group" title="Coxeter group">Coxeter group</a>, namely the number of fully commutative elements of the group; in terms of the associated <a href="/wiki/Root_system" title="Root system">root system</a>, it is the number of anti-chains (or order ideals) in the poset of positive roots. The classical Catalan number <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle C_{n}}">
